subSubSection.paragraph:
Body oval, moderately convex, dorsum covered with pale yellow pubescence (
Figs 7a–c
). Head, antennae and mouthparts yellow (
Fig. 7c
), tip of mandibles brown. Pronotum and scutellar shield yellow. Elytra black or dark brown, base margin and apical margin yellowish brown (
Figs 7a–c
). Prothoracic hypomeron and prosternum yellow. Mesoventrite black with yellowish brown base. Metaventrite black. Elytral epipleurae black or dark brown with yellowish brown base. Legs yellow.

Head with fine frontal punctures, as large as eye facets, 1.0–2.0 diameters apart. Eye densely faceted, interocular distance 0.25 times of head width (
Fig. 7c
). Inner ocular margin arcuate. Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 1.0–1.5 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.0 diameters.

Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and moderately recurved, reaching 3/4 length of ventrite 1 (
Fig. 7d
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, relatively narrowly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with weekly coarse and sparse punctures at middle.

Male genitalia. Penis short and stout, strongly curved at base, apical 1/3 of penis slightly swollen and narrowing to apex (
Fig. 7e
); tegmen with penis guide stout, parallel at basal 3/4 length, apical narrowing sharply in inner view (

Fig. 
7g

), shorter than 1/3 length of parameres; parameres large, elongate oval, apex with several setae (
Fig. 7f
).
